[[File:Fighting Chaos Fanatic.png|thumb|300px|A player faces the Chaos Fanatic.]]
The [[Chaos Fanatic]] is a relatively simple boss similar to the [[Crazy archaologist]] and the [[Deranged archaologist]];  his special attack has the potential to cause major damage if not avoided. 

Due to his high magic level and defensive bonuses, the most effective strategy is to use [[Ranged]] while [[Protect from Magic|protecting from magic]] and avoiding his green special attack by moving away from where you are standing.

Players can optionally walk to the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|altar]] that lies to the south-west in order to recharge their prayer after each fight, although this is a highly active [[player killing]] spot. Player killers can only attack you in between kills while waiting for the boss to respawn, so always be aware of players nearby who may be waiting for you to finish your kill.

In order to escape from player killers, a good option is to make use of the [[Wilderness obelisk]] to the north to teleport to level 13 Wilderness (possible to guarantee after completion of the [[Wilderness Diary#Hard|hard Wilderness Diary]]) which will then allow the player to teleport away using a standard [[teleport|teleport method]]. Players can also run east into the [[King Black Dragon Lair]] (non-Wilderness) and teleport from there.

